description._content: Note: A photograph showing almost the entire population of Mullumbimby in about 1893. Since then the town has become a centre of alternative culture and lifestyle, well known for the beauty of the rainforest and the proximity of beaches Format: Albumen photograph Notes: Find more detailed information about this photograph: acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/item/itemDetailPaged.aspx?itemID=411613 Search for more great images in the State Library's collections: acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/search/SimpleSearch.aspx From the collection of the State Library of New South Wales www.sl.nsw.gov.au
